		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="head" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						subtilitas in dictis, factisq[ue] singularis.
					</marginalia_text>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Subtlety in words and in singular deeds.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="IT">
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						ridicolo: ma aspramente.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Ridiculous, but bitterly.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						( Acies humani generis acutissima. )
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				The sharpest blade of the human race.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Subtilior ipso Doctore subtili.
						Aut intim&egrave; singula: aut omnia nihil.
					</marginalia_text>
					<person name="Duns Scotus"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				More subtle than the Subtle Doctor himself. <!--JG: I think you forgot part of the translation-->
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						Ante omnia, subtilitas in dictis, factisq[ue] super omnes. Nam et paucissimi sunt,
						qui aut dixeru[n]t, aut scripseru[n]t, aut egeru[n]t subtilissim&egrave;: et illi ipsi acutis dictis,
						profundis sententijs; callidis strategematibus, omniq[ue] egregiorum facinorum 
					</marginalia_text>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
					<emphasis method="chalk" type="straight"/>
				</position>
				<position place="right_margin" book_orientation="90">
					<marginalia_text>
						varietate facil&egrave; possunt superari. Nemo adhuc in vtilibus negocijs satis subtilis.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Before all other things, subtlety in words, and deeds beyond all other men. Indeed there are very few,
				who either spoke, or wrote, or did things in a most subtle manner, and those men themselves with their sharp words,
				profound opinions, cunning strategems, and every sort of excellent deed, can be easily surpassed by means of variety.
				Thus far, no one engaged in useful activities is subtle enough.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		
